ed tyre\", \"from\": 231, \"to\": 247}, {\"ngram\": \"a thrilling duel\", \"from\": 261, \"to\": 277}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic mountain bike title\", \"from\": 319, \"to\": 350}, {\"ngram\": \"bookmarks\", \"from\": 380, \"to\": 389}, {\"ngram\": \"offers\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 429}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 431, \"to\": 437}, {\"ngram\": \"updates\", \"from\": 442, \"to\": 449}, {\"ngram\": \"The Independent\", \"from\": 455, \"to\": 470}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice Three hundred and twenty-eight other gold medals will be handed out at these Paris Games, but surely none will be won asdramatically as this.Tom Pidcocklost the race to a puncture, won it back, then lost it again to the determined Frenchman Victor Koretzky before pulling off a do-or-die overtake around a tree todefend his Olympic title.\", \"from\": 476, \"to\": 838, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 741, \"end\": 756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Koretzky\", \"score\": 0.9999880939516794, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Victor Koretzky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Koretzky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Koretzky\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ourPrivacy notice\", \"from\": 481, \"to\": 498}, {\"ngram\": \"Three hundred and twenty-eight other gold medals\", \"from\": 499, \"to\": 547}, {\"ngram\": \"these Paris Games\", \"from\": 570, \"to\": 587}, {\"ngram\": \"none\", \"from\": 600, \"to\": 604}, {\"ngram\": \"Tom Pidcocklost\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 655}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 656, \"to\": 664}, {\"ngram\": \"a puncture\", \"from\": 668, \"to\": 678}, {\"ngram\": \"a do-or-die overtake\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 795}, {\"ngram\": \"a tree\", \"from\": 803, \"to\": 809}, {\"ngram\": \"his Olympic title\", \"from\": 819, \"to\": 836}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a superhuman display of racing.\", \"from\": 840, \"to\": 878, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a superhuman display\", \"from\": 847, \"to\": 867}, {\"ngram\": \"racing\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 877}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the third of eight 4.4km laps, Pidcock was forced to stand still for half a minute while a frazzled mechanic changed his punctured front tyre and rivals whizzed by.\", \"from\": 879, \"to\": 1046, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the third\", \"from\": 882, \"to\": 891}, {\"ngram\": \"eight 4.4km laps\", \"from\": 895, \"to\": 911}, {\"ngram\": \"Pidcock\", \"from\": 913, \"to\": 920}, {\"ngram\": \"half a minute\", \"from\": 951, \"to\": 964}, {\"ngram\": \"a frazzled mechanic\", \"from\": 971, \"to\": 990}, {\"ngram\": \"his punctured front tyre\", \"from\": 999, \"to\": 1023}, {\"ngram\": \"rivals\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1034}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He lost 36 seconds in all but soon began picking them off, one by one.\", \"from\": 1047, \"to\": 1117, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"36 seconds\", \"from\": 1055, \"to\": 1065}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Koretzky had watched Pidcock's race dismantle firsthand as he took the lead, so what must he have thought when he turned a hairpin four laps and 40 minutes later to see Pidcock reincarnated?\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1308, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Koretzky\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1126}, {\"ngram\": \"Pidcock's race\", \"from\": 1139, \"to\": 1153}, {\"ngram\": \"the lead\", \"from\": 1185, \"to\": 1193}, {\"ngram\": \"a hairpin\", \"from\": 1239, \"to\": 1248}, {\"ngram\": \"four laps\", \"from\": 1249, \"to\": 1258}, {\"ngram\": \"Pidcock\", \"from\": 1287, \"to\": 1294}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the final throes they went wheel to wheel, and in a wooded section of the course with trees peppering the middle of the track, Pidcock threw everything at gold, diving down the inside lane and emerging at the next bend half a wheel in front.\", \"from\": 1310, \"to\": 1554, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the final throes\", \"from\": 1313, \"to\": 1329}, {\"ngram\": \"wheel\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 1354}, {\"ngram\": \"a wooded section\", \"from\": 1363, \"to\": 1379}, {\"ngram\": \"the course\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1393}, {\"ngram\": \"trees\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1404}, {\"ngram\": \"the middle\", \"from\": 1415, \"to\": 1425}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 1429, \"to\": 1438}, {\"ngram\": \"Pidcock\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1447}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1464}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1468, \"to\": 1472}, {\"ngram\": \"the inside lane\", \"from\": 1486, \"to\": 1501}, {\"ngram\": \"the next bend\", \"from\": 1518, \"to\": 1531}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 1548, \"to\": 1553}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They came together and made contact, Koretzky's left foot was briefly dislodged from his pedal, and Pidcock sped away to emotional glory.\", \"from\": 1555, \"to\": 1692, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"contact\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1590}, {\"ngram\": \"Koretzky's left foot\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1612}, {\"ngram\": \"his pedal\", \"from\": 1640, \"to\": 1649}, {\"ngram\": \"Pidcock\", \"from\": 1655, \"to\": 1662}, {\"ngram\": \"emotional glory\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1691}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He fell into the arms of his family waiting at the finish, as some in the disappointed French crowd booed him.\", \"from\": 1694, \"to\": 1804, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1781, \"end\": 1787, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.6018234925799407, \"rank\": 0.5583176442626351, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the arms\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1715}, {\"ngram\": \"his family\", \"from\": 1719, \"to\": 1729}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish\", \"from\": 1741, \"to\": 1751}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They were understandably frustrated but Pidcock had done nothing wrong.\", \"from\": 1805, \"to\": 1876, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Pidcock\", \"from\": 1845, \"to\": 1852}, {\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 1862, \"to\": 1869}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I knew Victor was going to be strong, and then the puncture happened,\\\" Pidcock said afterwards, before revealing his inner monologue: a three-word pep-talk.\", \"from\": 1878, \"to\": 2035, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1886, \"end\": 1892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Newman\", \"score\": 0.9982301541899206, \"rank\": 0.0016180207282325896, \"text\": \"Victor\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Newman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Newman\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the puncture\", \"from\": 1926, \"to\": 1938}, {\"ngram\": \"Pidcock\", \"from\": 1950, \"to\": 1957}, {\"ngram\": \"his inner monologue\", \"from\": 1992, \"to\": 2011}, {\"ngram\": \"a three-word pep-talk\", \"from\": 2013, \"to\": 2034}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"At that point I just imagined when I did a little ride this morning that, when I punctured, I was just going to say 'f*** f*** f***' three times, slowly, calmly, and then I am just going to have to get on with it.\", \"from\": 2036, \"to\": 2250, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that point\", \"from\": 2040, \"to\": 2050}, {\"ngram\": \"a little ride\", \"from\": 2078, \"to\": 2091}, {\"ngram\": \"f\", \"from\": 2159, \"to\": 2160}, {\"ngram\": \"f\", \"from\": 2164, \"to\": 2165}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Bruno [his mechanic] wasn't ready in the pits but he did a fast change, and I knew at that point I had almost five laps, that's almost 50 minutes, so I thought, anything's possible.\\\"\", \"from\": 2252, \"to\": 2435, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Bruno\", \"from\": 2253, \"to\": 2258}, {\"ngram\": \"his mechanic\", \"from\": 2260, \"to\": 2272}, {\"ngram\": \"the pits\", \"from\": 2290, \"to\": 2298}, {\"ngram\": \"a fast change\", \"from\": 2310, \"to\": 2323}, {\"ngram\": \"that point\", \"from\": 2339, \"to\": 2349}, {\"ngram\": \"almost five laps\", \"from\": 2356, \"to\": 2372}, {\"ngram\": \"almost 50 minutes\", \"from\": 2381, \"to\": 2398}, {\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 2414, \"to\": 2422}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So Pidcock proved.\", \"from\": 2437, \"to\": 2455, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Pidcock\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2447}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is a double Olympic champion aged 24 - he turns 25 on Tuesday - something only a handful of Britons have achieved.\", \"from\": 2456, \"to\": 2573, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a double Olympic champion\", \"from\": 2462, \"to\": 2487}, {\"ngram\": \"Tuesday\", \"from\": 2513, \"to\": 2520}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 2523, \"to\": 2532}, {\"ngram\": \"only a handful\", \"from\": 2533, \"to\": 2547}, {\"ngram\": \"Britons\", \"from\": 2551, \"to\": 2558}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Adam Peaty was 25 when he defended his Olympic title; Andy Murray and Mo Farah were in their 30s.\", \"from\": 2574, \"to\": 2671, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2574, \"end\": 2584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}, {\"begin\": 2628, \"end\": 2639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.166128495531216e-41, \"text\": \"Andy Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 2644, \"end\": 2652, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mo_Farah\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mo Farah\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mo_Farah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mo_Farah\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his Olympic title\", \"from\": 2609, \"to\": 2626}, {\"ngram\": \"their 30s\", \"from\": 2661, \"to\": 2670}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pidcock's name will now be held in similar esteem.\", \"from\": 2672, \"to\": 2722, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Pidcock's name\", \"from\": 2672, \"to\": 2686}, {\"ngram\": \"similar esteem\", \"from\": 2707, \"to\": 2721}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Yorkshireman is an underappreciated jewel of British sport, perhaps because mountain biking does not carry a mainstream following.\", \"from\": 2724, \"to\": 2858, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2728, \"end\": 2740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yorkshire_County_Cricket_Club\", \"score\": 0.9990703833955065, \"rank\": 0.0009304813808524196, \"text\": \"Yorkshireman\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yorkshire_County_Cricket_Club\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yorkshire_County_Cricket_Club\"}, {\"begin\": 2773, \"end\": 2780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 0.9725075883926331, \"rank\": 0.023204403668371835, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an underappreciated jewel\", \"from\": 2744, \"to\": 2769}, {\"ngram\": \"mountain biking\", \"from\": 2804, \"to\": 2819}, {\"ngram\": \"a mainstream following\", \"from\": 2835, \"to\": 2857}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet his talents are multi-disciplined, as a cyclo-cross world champion and the winner of the queen stage of a Tour de France.\", \"from\": 2859, \"to\": 2984, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2969, \"end\": 2983, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 0.9999999989395292, \"rank\": 7.979172783683656e-10, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his talents\", \"from\": 2863, \"to\": 2874}, {\"ngram\": \"a cyclo-cross world champion\", \"from\": 2901, \"to\": 2929}, {\"ngram\": \"the winner\", \"from\": 2934, \"to\": 2944}, {\"ngram\": \"the queen stage\", \"from\": 2948, \"to\": 2963}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here he was up against mountain bike specialists, but that road race training with Ineos Grenadiers has developed his engine to go with the sublime, natural feel that makes him one of the best bike handlers in the world.\", \"from\": 2985, \"to\": 3205, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3068, \"end\": 3084, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ineos_Grenadiers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ineos Grenadiers\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ineos_Grenadiers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ineos_Grenadiers\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"mountain bike specialists\", \"from\": 3008, \"to\": 3033}, {\"ngram\": \"that road race training\", \"from\": 3039, \"to\": 3062}, {\"ngram\": \"his engine\", \"from\": 3099, \"to\": 3109}, {\"ngram\": \"the sublime, natural feel\", \"from\": 3121, \"to\": 3146}, {\"ngram\": \"the best bike handlers\", \"from\": 3169, \"to\": 3191}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3195, \"to\": 3204}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He needed that engine to haul himself back to Koretzky in 32C heat, but the winning moment, sending his bike up the inside of the split track, was pure racing instinct.\", \"from\": 3207, \"to\": 3375, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that engine\", \"from\": 3217, \"to\": 3228}, {\"ngram\": \"Koretzky\", \"from\": 3253, \"to\": 3261}, {\"ngram\": \"32C heat\", \"from\": 3265, \"to\": 3273}, {\"ngram\": \"the winning moment\", \"from\": 3279, \"to\": 3297}, {\"ngram\": \"his bike\", \"from\": 3307, \"to\": 3315}, {\"ngram\": \"the inside\", \"from\": 3319, \"to\": 3329}, {\"ngram\": \"the split track\", \"from\": 3333, \"to\": 3348}, {\"ngram\": \"pure racing instinct\", \"from\": 3354, \"to\": 3374}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In the end I just had to go for a gap.\", \"from\": 3377, \"to\": 3416, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 3381, \"to\": 3388}, {\"ngram\": \"a gap\", \"from\": 3410, \"to\": 3415}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rubbing is racing, that's what I have always done and the Olympics are no different.\", \"from\": 3417, \"to\": 3501, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3471, \"to\": 3483}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am sorry for [Koretzky], the support for him was incredible, but it's the Olympics.\", \"from\": 3502, \"to\": 3587, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Koretzky\", \"from\": 3518, \"to\": 3526}, {\"ngram\": \"the support\", \"from\": 3529, \"to\": 3540}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3574, \"to\": 3586}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You have to go all in.\\\"\", \"from\": 3588, \"to\": 3611, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pidcock had begun the race ensconced safely in the middle of the 36 riders before working his way through the pack, and by the third lap he led.\", \"from\": 3613, \"to\": 3757, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Pidcock\", \"from\": 3613, \"to\": 3620}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 3631, \"to\": 3639}, {\"ngram\": \"the middle\", \"from\": 3660, \"to\": 3670}, {\"ngram\": \"the 36 riders\", \"from\": 3674, \"to\": 3687}, {\"ngram\": \"his way\", \"from\": 3703, \"to\": 3710}, {\"ngram\": \"the pack\", \"from\": 3719, \"to\": 3727}, {\"ngram\": \"the third lap\", \"from\": 3736, \"to\": 3749}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But suddenly he was losing speed and control as the puncture struck, forcing him to clamber down a sheer drop carrying his bike as Koretzky flew off the ledge and into the lead.\", \"from\": 3758, \"to\": 3935, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"speed\", \"from\": 3785, \"to\": 3790}, {\"ngram\": \"control\", \"from\": 3795, \"to\": 3802}, {\"ngram\": \"the puncture\", \"from\": 3806, \"to\": 3818}, {\"ngram\": \"a sheer drop\", \"from\": 3855, \"to\": 3867}, {\"ngram\": \"his bike\", \"from\": 3877, \"to\": 3885}, {\"ngram\": \"Koretzky\", \"from\": 3889, \"to\": 3897}, {\"ngram\": \"the ledge\", \"from\": 3907, \"to\": 3916}, {\"ngram\": \"the lead\", \"from\": 3926, \"to\": 3934}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pidcock never faced this adversity three years in Tokyo, where he built a gap which grew into a dominant victory.\", \"from\": 3937, \"to\": 4050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3987, \"end\": 3992, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999974828688057, \"rank\": 2.503282217650535e-06, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Pidcock\", \"from\": 3937, \"to\": 3944}, {\"ngram\": \"this adversity\", \"from\": 3957, \"to\": 3971}, {\"ngram\": \"a gap\", \"from\": 4009, \"to\": 4014}, {\"ngram\": \"a dominant victory\", \"from\": 4031, \"to\": 4049}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But after swearing at himself he stayed calm, not charging to close the gap but refinding his rhythm and gradually eroding Koretzky's lead.\", \"from\": 4051, \"to\": 4190, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the gap\", \"from\": 4119, \"to\": 4126}, {\"ngram\": \"his rhythm\", \"from\": 4141, \"to\": 4151}, {\"ngram\": \"Koretzky's lead\", \"from\": 4174, \"to\": 4189}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French crowd had witnessed Pauline Ferrand-Prevot prevail on Sunday and were becoming frenzied at the thought of another mountain bike gold.\", \"from\": 4192, \"to\": 4336, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4196, \"end\": 4202, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.6018234925799407, \"rank\": 0.5583176442626351, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4223, \"end\": 4245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pauline_Ferrand-Pr\\u00e9vot\", \"score\": 0.9999998852631572, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pauline Ferrand-Prevot\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pauline_Ferrand-Pr\\u00e9vot\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pauline_Ferrand-Pr\\u00e9vot\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sunday\", \"from\": 4257, \"to\": 4263}, {\"ngram\": \"the thought\", \"from\": 4294, \"to\": 4305}, {\"ngram\": \"another mountain bike gold\", \"from\": 4309, \"to\": 4335}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps Koretzky felt the weight of their expectations when he lost control in the woods on lap seven, colliding with a tree and giving up his lead to the chasing Pidcock.\", \"from\": 4337, \"to\": 4508, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Koretzky\", \"from\": 4345, \"to\": 4353}, {\"ngram\": \"the weight\", \"from\": 4359, \"to\": 4369}, {\"ngram\": \"their expectations\", \"from\": 4373, \"to\": 4391}, {\"ngram\": \"control\", \"from\": 4405, \"to\": 4412}, {\"ngram\": \"the woods\", \"from\": 4416, \"to\": 4425}, {\"ngram\": \"lap\", \"from\": 4429, \"to\": 4432}, {\"ngram\": \"a tree\", \"from\": 4455, \"to\": 4461}, {\"ngram\": \"his lead\", \"from\": 4476, \"to\": 4484}, {\"ngram\": \"the chasing Pidcock\", \"from\": 4488, \"to\": 4507}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Koretzky recovered, fought back and surged clear into what seemed like an unassailable lead.\", \"from\": 4510, \"to\": 4602, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Koretzky\", \"from\": 4510, \"to\": 4518}, {\"ngram\": \"an unassailable lead\", \"from\": 4581, \"to\": 4601}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He appeared to have the reserves of energy, fuelled by home support, as Pidcock began to tire from his almighty effort.\", \"from\": 4603, \"to\": 4722, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the reserves\", \"from\": 4623, \"to\": 4635}, {\"ngram\": \"energy\", \"from\": 4639, \"to\": 4645}, {\"ngram\": \"home support\", \"from\": 4658, \"to\": 4670}, {\"ngram\": \"Pidcock\", \"from\": 4675, \"to\": 4682}, {\"ngram\": \"his almighty effort\", \"from\": 4702, \"to\": 4721}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the Briton stayed close enough to give himself one more shot, and he took it.\", \"from\": 4723, \"to\": 4804, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Briton\", \"from\": 4727, \"to\": 4737}, {\"ngram\": \"one more shot\", \"from\": 4774, \"to\": 4787}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 4806, \"to\": 5036, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4857, \"end\": 4868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.591353470220066e-20, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"thought-provoking conversations\", \"from\": 4811, \"to\": 4842}, {\"ngram\": \"their replies\", \"from\": 4885, \"to\": 4898}, {\"ngram\": \"the page\", \"from\": 4914, \"to\": 4922}, {\"ngram\": \"another page\", \"from\": 4938, \"to\": 4950}, {\"ngram\": \"the site\", \"from\": 4954, \"to\": 4962}, {\"ngram\": \"inPlease\", \"from\": 4990, \"to\": 4998}, {\"ngram\": \"you